<br>
****snip****<br>
CoFE Charter: <br>
<br>
Section 1: Loot Rules <br>
<br>
Section 1 Part A: <br>
<br>
All loot goes to Scout. <br>
<br>
Section 1 Part B: <br>
<br>
If Scout already has said loot then it will be immediately deemed unworthy for anyone in CoFE and will be promptly destroyed. <br>
<br>
Section 1 Part C: <br>
<br>
If Scout cannot use said loot it will also be promptly destroyed, as it is useless to the guild. <br>
<br>
Section 2: Courtesy <br>
<br>
Section 2 Part A: <br>
<br>
You will refer to Scout as &quot;King&quot; or &quot;The King&quot; at all times. <br>
<br>
Section 2 Part B: <br>
<br>
If Scout says &quot;Jump&quot; you will immediately stop what you are doing and begin pounding the jump key. This is to pay respect to The King. <br>
<br>
Section 2 Part C: <br>
<br>
If The King asks for a teleport all available teleporters will stop what they are doing and rush to The King. <br>
<br>
If you have an alt that can teleport, you must sit and log. <br>
<br>
Once everyone is at the scene, you must all begin pounding the jump key, and whoever The King deems as the best jumper, will be given the priveledge of teleporting The King. The rest must all bind themselves at the bottom of Lake Rathe and go into a death loop for as long as The King determines. <br>
<br>
Secton 4: Oops <br>
<br>
Section 4 Part A: <br>
<br>
The King does not make mistakes, he put Section 4 on purpose to catch you off guard, he is a wise and tricky man. <br>
<br>
Do not question his motives. <br>
<br>
Section 5: Raids <br>
<br>
Section 5 Part A: <br>
<br>
You will not attend any raids that The King himself cannot attend. Being level 27, we know this limits the raids you can go to, and The Management is looking into some way to fix this problem. It is working as intended until further notice. <br>
<br>
Section 5 Part B: <br>
<br>
If The King is not online you are free to raid anywhere you want, except in &quot;The King's No No Zones of the Week&quot;. These are zones The King determines as off limits each week, for no particular reason other than to be enigmatic. <br>
<br>
Do not question his motives. <br>
<br>
Section 6: Rezzes <br>
<br>
Section 6 Part A: <br>
<br>
If The King should happen to die he will be the only person rezzed. Everyone else who died will be allowed to run back to their corpse and loot it, but must destroy one piece of their equipment. Everyone who survives must bind at the bottom of Lake Rathe and de-level back to level 8. Level 8 was chosen because it seemed like a good round number to The King. <br>
<br>
Do not question his motives. <br>
<br>
Section 7: Everything Else <br>
<br>
I think that covers most of the bases. If The King.. I mean, if I think of anything else, I will be sure to let you know after you break the rule, and will promptly bind yourself at the bottom of Lake Rathe to be cleansed of your levels. <br>
<br>
****snip****<br>
<br>
