<br>
I do not consider myself the master of high-end game play, but once mobs start hitting for 2-300, it starts making sense to have NOBODY get hit except the person who you want to get hit.  If a frog in Sebilis hits you a few times, you take a little damage and you back up and the warrior hits Taunt and everything settles down.  If a wurm in Temple of Veeshan, or even a sufficiently large giant in the Arena in Kael hits you a few times...  ...you die.<br>
<br>
Then, once you've established that not only is it a good idea to have your guild's tanks...  ...well...  ...tank, then, soon, you get a cleric that says, hey, man, we got a 20 person raid here and I'm the only person healing... ...can you heal my guy too?<br>
<br>
Things snowball.  &quot;Hey, I'm healing this guy as fast as I can, but I can't keep up, can we BOTH heal him?&quot;  Ok, I'll cast, and then you cast.  If that's too much, we'll have some other guy cast inbetween us.<br>
<br>
Sooner or later you have 5 clerics grouped with a bard makin' mana; casting complete heal in a circle like they're passing a baton.<br>
<br>
Anyway, this might be remedial for most of you, but if you got this far and still wanted to learn something, there it is; the end sum of my knowledge on the subject *wink*. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,
